"------------------------------------------------------------
"------- MANDANTORY OPTIONS ---------------------------------
"------------------------------------------------------------

" set 'nocompatible' to ward off unexpected things
set nocompatible

" disable modeline for security reasons
set nomodeline


"------------------------------------------------------------
"------- INDENTATION OPTIONS --------------------------------
"------------------------------------------------------------

" attempt to determine the type of a file based on its name and possibly its
" contents. use this to allow intelligent auto-indenting for each filetype,
" and for plugins that are filetype specific.
filetype indent plugin on

" when opening a new line and no filetype-specific indenting is enabled, keep
" the same indent as the line you're currently on.
set autoindent

" use spaces instead of tabs
set expandtab

" one tab equals four spaces
set shiftwidth=4
set softtabstop=4



" ------- SEARCH OPTIONS -------

" highlight search matches
set hlsearch

" incremental search
set incsearch

" use case insensitive search unless they contain at least one capital letter
set ignorecase
set smartcase



" ------- GUI OPTIONS -------

" display line numbers on the left
set number

" use relative line numbers
set relativenumber

"always display the status line
set laststatus=2

"indicate lines longer than 80 characters
highlight OverLength ctermbg=darkgrey ctermfg=white guibg=#FFD9D9
match OverLength /\%>80v.\+/

"use a colorscheme 
"(using a colorscheme will reset all highlight groups from outside that scheme's scope.
"prefer to choose nice colours for the terminal emulator)
" colorscheme darcula



" ------- SYNTAX OPTIONS -------

" enable syntax highlighting
syntax on



" ------- MISCELLANEOUS OPTIONS -------

set noswapfile  " disable swapfile




"======> sammelbecken von m√∂glichen optionen:

" sth for trailing whitespace

" always show current position
"set ruler

" better command-line completion
"set wildmenu

" Set to auto read when a file is changed from the outside
"set autoread

"set hidden

